[Gemini]: This review focuses on potential HTTP request smuggling vulnerabilities in `aiohttp`'s HTTP parser, stemming from non-compliance with RFC 9110 and RFC 9112. I will begin by investigating the `Content-Length` parsing issues highlighted by the first query, as these are critical for preventing desynchronization attacks. My first step is to examine the code at `aiohttp/http_parser.py`, line 326, to verify if `int()` is used on the header value without proper validation.

